JOHANNESBURG - Barend Bester is the only South Africa to have qualified for the BWF World Para-Badminton Championships in Switzerland. The tournament will be from 20th to the 25th August with around 50 nations battling it out. Bester has qualified in the men’s singles category and ranks 52nd in the world. He’s also the first South African to compete in the Para-World Championships. “I would have loved to play doubles and mixed doubles as well,” said Bester. Para-badminton will be a Paralympic sport from 2020 onwards. Bester hopes to qualify for Tokyo at the World Championships. - Palesa Manaleng